               <msContents>
                  <summary>I-1) Maṣḥafa śǝrʿāt, The introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols.
                     5ra-6va)&#xD; I-2) ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki “I worship Thee…” (fols.
                     6va-7ra)&#xD; I-3) Taʾāmra Māryām “Miracles of Mary”: 93 miracles (fols.
                     2ra-4vb, 7ra-77ra)&#xD; II) Taʾāmra Mikāʾel "Miracles of Michael": 1 miracle
                     (fols. 77rb-77vb)&#xD; &#xD; Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1"> f. 77ra: ዘንቱ፡ ተአምር፡ ዘአጽሐፋ፡ በትግሐቱ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ። በ፵፡
                     ብር። [<locus target="#77rb">77rb</locus>] ተጽሕፈ፡ በዘመነ፡ አቡነ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አባ፡ ቄርሎስ፡
                     ወብፁዕ፡ ጳጳስ፡ አባ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወበዘመነ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ምኒልክ፡ በ፶፻{ወ}፭፻፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፲ወ፬፡ ዓመተ፡
                     ምሕረት። ዘወሀበቶ፡ ወለተ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በስልጣነ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡
                     ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ። The colophon states that the Ms. was commissioned by Gabra Giyorgis
                     and donated to the church by Walatta Libānos. It tells that the Ms. was written
                     in 1914 year of mercy (= 1921/22 A.D.), but also refers to King Mǝnilǝk II (r.
                     1889-1913), Patriarch Cyril V of Alexandria (in tenure in 1874-1927) and
                     Metropolitan Ṗeṭros (in tenure in 1881-1917). </colophon>
               </msContents>
